data.content:
`Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi 10.0` pulls in `Microsoft.OpenApi` v2.x which has several breaking changes affecting your code. Here's each issue and fix:

**1. Namespaces removed** — `Microsoft.OpenApi.Models` and `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` no longer exist:
```csharp
// Before
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;

// After
using Microsoft.OpenApi;
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
```

**2. `OpenApiString` removed** — Use `JsonNode`:
```csharp
// Before
param.Schema.Example = new OpenApiString("1.0");

// After
param.Schema.Example = JsonNode.Parse("\"1.0\"");
```

**3. `OpenApiSecurityScheme.Reference` replaced** — Use `OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference`:
```csharp
// Before
var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecurityScheme
{
    Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }
};

// After
var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2", null);
```

**4. Collections are now nullable** — `Parameters`, `Responses`, etc. may be null:
```csharp
// Before
var param = operation.Parameters.FirstOrDefault(...);
operation.Responses.TryAdd(...);

// After
var param = operation.Parameters?.FirstOrDefault(...);
operation.Responses ??= new OpenApiResponses();
operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });
```

**5. `OpenApiSchema.Nullable` removed** — OpenAPI 3.1 uses JSON Schema's `type: ["string", "null"]` instead of `nullable: true`. Your schema transformer setting `.Nullable = false` can simply be deleted — the property no longer exists.

**6. Security requirement values** — Ensure `scopes` is a `List<string>`:
```csharp
[oAuthScheme] = scopes.ToList()
```

### Fully migrated code

```csharp
using Microsoft.OpenApi;
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters?.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        param.Schema.Example = JsonNode.Parse("\"1.0\"");
    }

    operation.Responses ??= new OpenApiResponses();
    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2", null);
    operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
    {
        new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes.ToList() }
    };

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

// The schema transformer setting Nullable can be removed entirely,
// or simplified to only handle other property logic if needed.
```
